HEADWORD: Musicomania
<hw>Mu`si*co*ma"ni*a</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Music</ets> + <ets>mania</ets>: cf. F.
<ets>musicomanie</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A kind of
monomania in which the passion for music becomes so strong as to derange
the intellectual faculties.</def> <rj><au>Dunglison.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
